After a sloppy game between the Jets and the Arizona Cardinals, which was due to bad weather, the second quarter began.
However, when quarterback Brett Favres' pass came to Lavernues Coles for a 12-yard touchdown, it marked the perfect start to an afternoon when their evolving partnership took a giant leap forward.
Favre found Coles in that quarter for two more touchdowns, one slipping out as a pinch hitter and the other 10 seconds into the half.
"I didn't really try", Coles says of the passes that went to Coles.
"He's a super player.
Our vote was a success, no matter what people think".
While Favre and Cole were playing catch, defensive quarterback Kurt Warner was taking a swing.
Outfielder Darrelle Revis intercepted a missed throw and converted it into a 32-yard touchdown.
Libero Erik Smith came to another pass and caught him.
Linebacker David Bowens then took a loss to Warner.
The last ball loss forced on Bowens was probably the craziest.
The Cardinals had the ball with 10 seconds left in the game when the Jets recaptured the ball and Jay Feely converted a 20-yard field goal to take a 34-0 lead.
That was the most points the Jets had ever scored in a quarter.
