Gary Glitter, the glam rock star convicted of child sexual abuse, has been banned from traveling to France and Spain.
Judges suspended Glitter for six months after he informed the authorities that he was traveling to Spain via France.
Kent police were granted permission last Thursday to impose a travel ban after presenting evidence to judges of Glitter's criminal record for child sexual abuse.
Glitter, whose real name is Paul Gadd, did not attend the hearing at Ashford County Court in Kent, but was represented by the law firm of Corker Binning.
