MP3 player accused of damaging hearing
Long-term exposure to loud music on portable music devices, such as MP3 players, can lead to permanent hearing damage.
This is reported by the European Commission, which in a report published today in Brussels quotes the opinion of the EU CSRSERI (Scientific Committee on Current and Recently Identified Health Risks).
"The report  states in a note  that it is clear that 5-10% of those who listen to loud music for more than an hour a day on a weekly basis with portable music devices for at least five years are at risk of permanent hearing loss".
